        "objection_en": "Quantum mechanics shows things can come into existence without a cause.",
        "response_zh": "量子真空涨落并非“从无中生有“。量子真空本身就是一种物理实在，具有结构和能量。真正的“无“（philosophical nothing）没有任何属性——没有量子场，没有物理定律，没有潜力。从绝对的无中，什么都不可能产生。此外，即使量子事件是非决定性的，它们仍然发生在已有的因果框架之内。",
        "response_en": "Quantum vacuum fluctuations are not creation from nothing. The quantum vacuum is itself a physical reality with structure and energy. True 'nothing' (philosophical nothing) has no properties — no quantum fields, no physical laws, no potentiality. From absolute nothing, nothing can come. Moreover, even if quantum events are indeterministic, they still occur within an existing causal framework."
