        "objection_en": "Maybe the universe is eternal, oscillating in cycles.",
        "response_zh": "热力学第二定律（熵增定律）表明宇宙的可用能量在不断减少。如果宇宙是永恒的，它早就应该达到热寂（heat death）了。此外，Borde-Guth-Vilenkin定理证明，任何平均膨胀的宇宙都必须有一个过去的时空边界。即使在多元宇宙假说中，这个定理依然成立。",
        "response_en": "The Second Law of Thermodynamics shows the universe's usable energy is constantly decreasing. If the universe were eternal, it would have reached heat death long ago. Furthermore, the Borde-Guth-Vilenkin theorem proves that any universe which has, on average, been expanding must have a past spacetime boundary. This holds even in multiverse scenarios."
