    "topic_zh": "圣经的可靠性：回应伊斯兰的“篡改论“",
    "topic_en": "Biblical Reliability: Responding to the Islamic Corruption Charge (Tahrif)",
    "core_argument_zh": "穆斯林常声称圣经已被篡改（Tahrif），但这与古兰经自身的教导矛盾。古兰经多次确认之前经典的权威性（5:46-47, 10:94, 3:3-4），命令穆斯林参考之前的经文。如果圣经已被篡改，古兰经确认一部被篡改的经文就动摇了自身可靠性。\n\n死海古卷的发现具有决定性意义。1947年发现的这些手稿比之前已知的最早希伯来文旧约手稿早约1000年，却与后来的马索拉文本几乎完全一致，证明旧约在超过千年传抄中保持了极高准确性。\n\n古兰经创造了自我矛盾的困境：如果圣经在穆罕默德时代可靠（古兰经暗示如此），那么当时与今天基本相同的圣经清楚教导耶稣的神性和十字架救赎。如果圣经更早被篡改，古兰经确认被篡改的经文就是错误的。无论哪种情况伊斯兰立场都面临内在矛盾。\n\n新约学者梅茨格和华莱士的研究表明新约手稿证据远超任何其他古代文献——超过5800份希腊文手稿、10000+份拉丁文手稿。文本批判学能以极高精度重建原文。",
    "core_argument_en": "Muslims often claim the Bible was corrupted (Tahrif), but this contradicts the Quran itself, which repeatedly affirms previous scriptures' authority (5:46-47, 10:94, 3:3-4) and commands consulting them. If the Bible was corrupted, the Quran affirming a corrupted text undermines its own reliability.\n\nThe Dead Sea Scrolls are decisive. Found in 1947, these manuscripts predate the previously earliest known Hebrew OT manuscripts by ~1,000 years, yet are nearly identical to the later Masoretic Text, proving extremely high accuracy over millennia of copying.\n\nThe Quran creates a self-contradictory dilemma: if the Bible was reliable in Muhammad's time (the Quran implies this), then that Bible — textually identical to today's — clearly teaches Jesus' deity and the Cross's atonement. If the Bible was corrupted earlier, the Quran affirming a corrupted text is erroneous. Either way, the Islamic position faces internal contradiction.\n\nNT scholars Metzger and Wallace show NT manuscript evidence far surpasses any other ancient document — over 5,800 Greek manuscripts, 10,000+ Latin manuscripts. Textual criticism reconstructs the original with extremely high precision.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "古兰经说的是意思被篡改（Tahrif al-Ma'na），不是文本被改变。",
        "objection_en": "The Quran refers to corruption of meaning (Tahrif al-Ma'na), not textual alteration.",
        "response_zh": "即使只是“意思的篡改“，古兰经仍然命令穆斯林去参考“手中的经文“（5:68, 10:94），这意味着文本本身仍然是可靠的。此外，如果我们接受文本完好但意思被误解，那唯一的解决办法就是回去阅读文本本身——这恰恰是基督徒在做的事。当穆斯林读了圣经原文，他们会发现耶稣的神性、十字架的救赎、三位一体等核心教义贯穿始终。",
        "response_en": "Even if only 'meaning corruption,' the Quran still commands Muslims to consult 'the Scripture in their hands' (5:68, 10:94), implying the text itself remains reliable. If we accept the text is intact but meaning is misunderstood, the solution is to read the text itself — which is exactly what Christians do. When Muslims read the biblical text, they find the deity of Christ, the atonement of the Cross, and the Trinity taught throughout."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "圣经有不同的版本和手稿差异，怎么能说没被改？",
        "objection_en": "The Bible has different versions and manuscript variants — how can it be uncorrupted?",
        "response_zh": "手稿差异恰恰证明了文本批判学的成功，而非圣经的失败。我们拥有超过5,800份新约希腊文手稿，加上数万份译本和教父引用。绝大多数差异是拼写和抄写错误，不影响任何教义。通过比较这些手稿，学者可以高度精确地还原原文。相比之下，古兰经的乌斯曼标准化过程中，哈里发奥斯曼下令烧毁了所有其他版本。",
        "response_en": "Manuscript variants actually demonstrate the success of textual criticism, not the Bible's failure. We possess over 5,800 Greek NT manuscripts, plus tens of thousands of translations and patristic citations. The vast majority of variants are spelling and scribal errors affecting no doctrine. By comparing manuscripts, scholars can reconstruct the original with high accuracy. By contrast, during the Uthmanic standardization of the Quran, Caliph Uthman ordered all other versions burned."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "也许篡改发生在穆罕默德之后，而不是之前。",
        "objection_en": "Perhaps the corruption happened after Muhammad, not before.",
        "response_zh": "这个说法缺乏任何历史证据。我们拥有的圣经手稿远早于穆罕默德时代——死海古卷（公元前2世纪至公元1世纪）、抄本（如4世纪的西奈抄本和梵蒂冈抄本）——它们与我们今天的圣经在文本上基本一致。如果篡改发生在穆罕默德之后，需要一个不可能的全球性阴谋：同时修改分散在从英国到埃塞俄比亚、从叙利亚到印度的数千份手稿，而且不留下任何证据。这比复活本身更难以置信。",
        "response_en": "This claim lacks any historical evidence. Biblical manuscripts far predate Muhammad — the Dead Sea Scrolls (2nd century BC to 1st century AD), codices like the 4th-century Codex Sinaiticus and Vaticanus — are textually consistent with today's Bible. Post-Muhammad corruption would require an impossible global conspiracy: simultaneously altering thousands of manuscripts scattered from Britain to Ethiopia, Syria to India, leaving no evidence. This is more incredible than the resurrection itself."
      }
    ],
