  {
    "id": "islam-002",
    "target_worldview": "islam",
    "topic_zh": "耶稣的神性：回应伊斯兰对三位一体的误解",
    "topic_en": "The Deity of Christ: Answering Islamic Misunderstandings of the Trinity",
    "core_argument_zh": "伊斯兰教认为三位一体是多神论，但这源于对基督教教义的根本误解。古兰经（5:116）暗示三位一体是\"真主、耶稣和马利亚\"，这从未是基督教的教导。正统基督教信仰的三位一体是：一位上帝，三个位格——圣父、圣子、圣灵——本质相同，位格有别。这不是三个神，而是一位上帝在三个位格中永恒地存在。\n\n耶稣的神性有坚实的历史和圣经根据。在约翰福音8:58，耶稣宣称\"还没有亚伯拉罕，我就是（I AM）\"，直接引用出埃及记3:14上帝的自称。犹太领袖准确理解了这一宣称的含义——他们拿石头要打他，因为这是\"僭妄\"的话（约翰福音10:33）。托马斯在耶稣复活后宣告：\"我的主！我的上帝！\"（约翰福音20:28），耶稣坦然接受了这一敬拜。\n\n拉里·赫塔多（Larry Hurtado）在《主耶稣基督》中考证，对耶稣的敬拜在基督教运动最初二十年内就已出现，这在严格一神论的犹太背景下是惊人的。理查德·鲍克汉（Richard Bauckham）在《耶稣与以色列的上帝》中论证，早期基督徒将耶稣纳入上帝的独一身份中，而非视为次等神灵。腓立比书2:6-11的基督颂歌——公认为极早期的信仰告白——宣告耶稣\"本有上帝的形像\"，且配得\"万膝跪拜\"的敬拜，这在旧约中专属耶和华（以赛亚书45:23）。歌罗西书1:16-17更宣告万有都是靠基督造的，又是为他造的——这是只属于创造者上帝的属性。",
    "core_argument_en": "Islam considers the Trinity polytheistic, but this stems from a fundamental misunderstanding of Christian doctrine. The Quran (5:116) implies the Trinity consists of 'God, Jesus, and Mary' — this was never Christian teaching. Orthodox Christian faith confesses one God in three persons — Father, Son, and Holy Spirit — same essence, distinct persons. This is not three gods but one God eternally existing in three persons.\n\nJesus's divinity rests on solid historical and biblical foundations. In John 8:58, Jesus declared 'Before Abraham was, I AM,' directly invoking God's self-designation from Exodus 3:14. The Jewish leaders understood precisely — they took up stones to kill him for 'blasphemy' (John 10:33). Thomas declared to the risen Jesus: 'My Lord and my God!' (John 20:28), and Jesus accepted this worship.\n\nLarry Hurtado in 'Lord Jesus Christ' demonstrates that worship of Jesus emerged within the first twenty years of the Christian movement — astonishing within strict Jewish monotheism. Richard Bauckham in 'Jesus and the God of Israel' argues early Christians included Jesus within God's unique identity rather than treating him as a lesser deity. The Christ hymn in Philippians 2:6-11 — recognized as a very early creed — declares Jesus existed 'in the form of God' and deserves worship where 'every knee should bow,' language reserved for YHWH alone in Isaiah 45:23. Colossians 1:16-17 further declares all things were created through and for Christ — an attribute belonging only to the Creator God.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶稣自己从未说“我是上帝“。",
        "objection_en": "Jesus never said 'I am God.'",
        "response_zh": "耶稣以第一世纪犹太人能理解的方式宣告了祂的神性：（1）使用“I AM“（ego eimi）自称，直接引用出埃及记3:14上帝的圣名（约翰福音8:58）；（2）宣告赦罪的权柄——只有上帝能赦罪（马可福音2:5-7）；（3）宣称自己是安息日的主（马可福音2:28）；（4）接受“我的主、我的上帝“的敬拜（约翰福音20:28）。犹太领袖正是因为这些宣告要将祂治死（约翰福音5:18）。",
        "response_en": "Jesus declared His deity in ways first-century Jews understood: (1) Using 'I AM' (ego eimi), directly referencing God's name in Exodus 3:14 (John 8:58); (2) Claiming authority to forgive sins — which only God can do (Mark 2:5-7); (3) Declaring Himself Lord of the Sabbath (Mark 2:28); (4) Accepting worship as 'My Lord and my God' (John 20:28). The Jewish leaders sought to kill Him precisely for these claims (John 5:18)."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "三位一体不合逻辑——1+1+1=3，不是1。",
        "objection_en": "The Trinity is illogical — 1+1+1=3, not 1.",
        "response_zh": "这误解了三位一体的含义。基督教并非说三个神等于一个神（那确实矛盾）。而是说：一个神的本质（being/essence），存在于三个位格（persons）中。本质和位格是不同的范畴。数学类比应该是1x1x1=1，而非1+1+1。更准确地说，三位一体超越了简单的数学类比——它反映了上帝本体中的关系性存在，这是一神论中独特的深度。",
        "response_en": "This misunderstands the Trinity. Christianity doesn't claim three Gods equal one God (that would be contradictory). Rather: one divine essence (being) exists in three Persons. Essence and person are different categories. The mathematical analogy should be 1×1×1=1, not 1+1+1. More precisely, the Trinity transcends simple mathematical analogies — it reflects relational existence within God's being, a unique depth within monotheism."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶稣只是一位先知（nabi），就像穆萨和易卜拉欣一样。",
        "objection_en": "Jesus was merely a prophet (nabi), like Moses and Abraham.",
        "response_zh": "耶稣远超先知的角色。先知说“耶和华如此说“，耶稣说“我告诉你们“（马太福音5:21-22）。先知敬拜上帝，耶稣接受敬拜。先知会死，耶稣从死里复活且有权柄赐人永生（约翰福音11:25）。甚至古兰经也赋予耶稣独特的地位：童贞女所生、行神迹、被称为“上帝的道“（Kalimatullah）和“上帝的灵“（Ruhullah）——这些称号从未给予其他先知。",
        "response_en": "Jesus far exceeds the role of a prophet. Prophets say 'Thus says the Lord'; Jesus says 'I say to you' (Matthew 5:21-22). Prophets worship God; Jesus receives worship. Prophets die; Jesus rose from the dead and has authority to give eternal life (John 11:25). Even the Quran gives Jesus unique status: virgin-born, miracle-worker, called 'Word of God' (Kalimatullah) and 'Spirit of God' (Ruhullah) — titles never given to any other prophet."
      }
