        "response_zh": "保罗在罗马书6:1-2已经回应了这个问题：'我们可以仍在罪中、叫恩典显多吗？断乎不可！'真正经历恩典的人会被恩典改变。一个被从溺水中救出的人不会想跳回水里。恩典不仅赦免罪，还赐予新的生命和渴望圣洁的心（以西结书36:26-27）。改革宗神学强调：得救是唯独因信（sola fide），但真正的信心必然产生善行的果子。",
        "response_en": "Paul already addresses this in Romans 6:1-2: 'Are we to continue in sin that grace may abound? By no means!' Those who truly experience grace are transformed by it. Someone rescued from drowning doesn't want to jump back in. Grace not only forgives sin but gives new life and a heart that desires holiness (Ezekiel 36:26-27). Reformed theology emphasizes: salvation is by faith alone (sola fide), but true faith necessarily produces the fruit of good works."
      },
