    "id": "cults-001",
    "target_worldview": "cults",
    "topic_zh": "耶和华见证人：耶稣是被造的天使长？",
    "topic_en": "Jehovah's Witnesses: Is Jesus a Created Archangel?",
    "core_argument_zh": "耶和华见证人（守望台）最核心的错误是否认耶稣基督的完全神性，将耶稣降格为受造的天使长米迦勒。然而圣经清楚教导耶稣是上帝：约翰福音1:1\"道就是上帝\"，托马斯向复活的耶稣宣告\"我的主，我的上帝\"（约翰福音20:28），以赛亚9:6称弥赛亚为\"全能的上帝\"。\n\n耶和华见证人的《新世界译本》将约翰福音1:1改译为\"道是一个神\"，但这在希腊文法上站不住脚。科尔韦尔规则（Colwell's Rule）表明，前置的无冠词谓词名词通常是限定性的，因此原文的意思就是\"道就是上帝\"，而非\"一个神\"。几乎所有主流希腊文学者都拒绝守望台的翻译。\n\n否认基督神性对救恩有致命后果。如果耶稣只是受造之物，他就不可能为全人类的无限罪债提供足够的赎价——只有无限的上帝才能支付无限的代价。以赛亚43:11上帝宣告\"除我以外没有救主\"，而新约称耶稣为救主（提多书2:13）——这只有在耶稣就是上帝的情况下才不矛盾。\n\n守望台还因多次预言末日日期（1914、1925、1975等）均落空而严重损害了其可信度。按照申命记18:21-22的标准，假先知的特征就是预言不应验。",
    "core_argument_en": "Jehovah's Witnesses' (Watchtower's) most fundamental error is denying Jesus Christ's full deity, reducing Him to the created archangel Michael. But Scripture clearly teaches Jesus is God: John 1:1 'the Word was God,' Thomas declared to the risen Jesus 'My Lord and my God' (John 20:28), Isaiah 9:6 calls the Messiah 'Mighty God.'\n\nThe JW's New World Translation renders John 1:1 as 'the Word was a god,' but this is grammatically untenable in Greek. Colwell's Rule indicates that preverbal anarthrous predicate nominatives are typically definite, so the text means 'the Word was God,' not 'a god.' Virtually all mainstream Greek scholars reject the Watchtower translation.\n\nDenying Christ's deity has fatal soteriological consequences. If Jesus were merely created, He could not provide sufficient atonement for all humanity's infinite sin-debt — only the infinite God can pay an infinite price. Isaiah 43:11 declares 'besides me there is no savior,' while the NT calls Jesus Savior (Titus 2:13) — consistent only if Jesus is God.\n\nThe Watchtower has also severely damaged its credibility through multiple failed end-times predictions (1914, 1925, 1975, etc.). By the standard of Deuteronomy 18:21-22, the hallmark of a false prophet is unfulfilled prophecy.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "歌罗西书1:15说耶稣是“一切受造物的首生“——说明祂是被造的。",
        "objection_en": "Colossians 1:15 says Jesus is 'the firstborn of all creation' — so He was created.",
        "response_zh": "'首生'（prōtotokos）在希腊文和旧约中表示地位和优先权，不表示'第一个被造'。诗篇89:27称大卫为'首生的'，虽然他是耶西最小的儿子。紧接着歌罗西书1:16-17说明了为什么：'因为万有都是靠祂造的...祂在万有之先'。'首生'表示祂拥有对一切受造物的主权和优先地位。如果保罗想说'第一个被造的'，他会用'prōtoktistos'，但他没有。",
        "response_en": "'Firstborn' (prōtotokos) in Greek and the OT denotes rank and preeminence, not 'first created.' Psalm 89:27 calls David 'firstborn' though he was Jesse's youngest son. Colossians 1:16-17 immediately explains why: 'For by him all things were created... He is before all things.' 'Firstborn' indicates sovereign preeminence over all creation. Had Paul meant 'first created,' he would have used 'prōtoktistos' — but he didn't."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "约翰福音14:28耶稣说“父是比我大的“——说明耶稣不是上帝。",
        "objection_en": "In John 14:28, Jesus says 'the Father is greater than I' — proving He's not God.",
        "response_zh": "这里的'大'（meizon）指的是职能上的关系，不是本质上的差异。在三位一体中，圣子在永恒中自愿顺服圣父（经世关系/economic Trinity），但在本质上与圣父完全同等（本体关系/ontological Trinity）。耶稣在道成肉身的状态下说这话，指的是祂在地上的卑微地位。同一卷福音书中，耶稣也说'我与父原为一'（约翰福音10:30）。经文必须以经文来解释。",
        "response_en": "The word 'greater' (meizon) refers to functional relationship, not ontological difference. Within the Trinity, the Son voluntarily submits to the Father in the economic Trinity, while being fully equal in essence in the ontological Trinity. Jesus spoke this during His incarnate state, referring to His humbled earthly position. In the same Gospel, Jesus also says 'I and the Father are one' (John 10:30). Scripture must interpret Scripture."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶和华见证人也做了很多善事——探访病人、传讲圣经，怎么能说他们是异端？",
        "objection_en": "Jehovah's Witnesses do many good things — visiting the sick, preaching the Bible. How can they be called heretical?",
        "response_zh": "善行不能作为教义正确性的检验标准。耶稣在马太福音7:22-23中警告说，有人会奉他的名行许多善事，但他会说'我从来不认识你们'。核心问题不是行为，而是关于基督身份的真理。如果耶稣不是上帝而只是被造的天使长，那么基督教的整个救赎体系就崩溃了——因为只有上帝才能为全人类的罪提供足够的赎价。耶和华见证人否认基督的神性，这不是次要分歧，而是触及了福音的核心。",
        "response_en": "Good deeds cannot serve as a test for doctrinal correctness. Jesus warned in Matthew 7:22-23 that some will do many good deeds in His name, yet He will say 'I never knew you.' The core issue is not behavior but truth about Christ's identity. If Jesus is not God but merely a created archangel, the entire Christian redemption system collapses — because only God can provide sufficient atonement for all humanity's sin. JW's denial of Christ's deity is not a secondary disagreement but strikes at the Gospel's core."
      }
    ],
