        "response_en": "The issue isn't whether God 'can' but what He 'said.' Hebrews 9:28 says Christ was 'offered once.' Hebrews 10:12 says He 'offered for all time a single sacrifice for sins.' Christ's incarnation and atonement were once-for-all, perfect, unrepeatable. The manner of His return is clearly revealed: coming on clouds, every eye will see Him (Revelation 1:7). Any 'second coming' inconsistent with this is counterfeit."
