  {
    "id": "sec-001",
    "target_worldview": "secularism",
    "topic_zh": "科学与信仰：冲突还是互补？",
    "topic_en": "Science and Faith: Conflict or Complement?",
    "core_argument_zh": "科学方法论自然主义（在科学研究中假设自然原因）是合理的方法论工具，但将其扩展为形而上学自然主义（一切存在的只有自然界）则是一个未经证明的哲学跳跃。科学方法本身不能证明超自然不存在——这超出了科学的方法论范围。\n\n许多伟大的科学家同时是虔诚的基督徒：开普勒、牛顿、法拉第、麦克斯韦、普朗克、海森堡、弗朗西斯·柯林斯（人类基因组计划负责人）。科学和信仰的\"冲突叙事\"是19世纪末约翰·威廉·德雷珀和安德鲁·迪克森·怀特制造的历史神话，当代科学史学家已广泛否定了这一叙事。\n\n事实上，基督教为现代科学的诞生提供了必要的思想基础：（1）宇宙是有序的，因为它是一位理性的上帝所创造的；（2）研究自然界是有价值的，因为它是上帝的创造；（3）人有能力理解自然规律，因为人按上帝的形象被造。这些信念在其他世界观中并非不言自明——在泛神论中，自然界是神圣的，不应被\"解剖\"研究；在无神论中，没有理由假设宇宙是有序可知的。\n\n阿尔文·普兰丁格在《科学与宗教：它们真的冲突吗？》中论证，真正的冲突不是科学与信仰之间，而是自然主义与科学之间——因为如果按照自然主义的假设，我们的认知能力是盲目进化过程的产物，我们就没有理由信任它们能产生真信念，包括关于自然主义本身的信念。",
    "core_argument_en": "Methodological naturalism (assuming natural causes in scientific inquiry) is a reasonable methodological tool, but extending it to metaphysical naturalism (all that exists is nature) is an unproven philosophical leap. Science itself cannot prove the supernatural doesn't exist — this exceeds science's methodological scope.\n\nMany great scientists were devout Christians: Kepler, Newton, Faraday, Maxwell, Planck, Heisenberg, Francis Collins (Human Genome Project director). The science-faith 'conflict narrative' is a late-19th-century myth created by John William Draper and Andrew Dickson White, widely rejected by contemporary historians of science.\n\nIn fact, Christianity provided modern science's necessary intellectual foundations: (1) The universe is orderly because created by a rational God; (2) Studying nature is valuable as God's creation; (3) Humans can understand natural laws because made in God's image. These beliefs aren't self-evident in other worldviews — in pantheism, nature is divine and shouldn't be 'dissected'; in atheism, there's no reason to assume the universe is orderly and knowable.\n\nAlvin Plantinga in 'Where the Conflict Really Lies' argues the real conflict isn't between science and faith but between naturalism and science — because if, as naturalism assumes, our cognitive faculties are products of blind evolutionary processes, we have no reason to trust them to produce true beliefs, including beliefs about naturalism itself.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "进化论已经解释了生命的起源，不需要上帝。",
        "objection_en": "Evolution explains the origin of life; God is unnecessary.",
        "response_zh": "首先，进化假说试图解释的是生命的多样性（生物如何从简单变复杂），而非生命的起源（非生命如何变成生命）。生命起源仍是科学中的未解之谜。其次，宏观进化本身仍是一个假说，面临着寒武纪大爆发、不可还原的复杂性、生物信息起源等重大科学挑战。即使许多科学家持有这一假说，这并不等于它已被证实。微观进化（物种内的适应变化）是可观察的事实，但从单细胞到人类的宏观进化从未被直接观察到。基督徒不必因为进化假说而质疑创造者的存在。",
        "response_en": "First, the evolutionary hypothesis attempts to explain the diversity of life (how organisms became complex), not the origin of life (how non-life became life). The origin of life remains an unsolved mystery in science. Second, macro-evolution itself remains a hypothesis facing major scientific challenges including the Cambrian Explosion, irreducible complexity, and the origin of biological information. Even though many scientists hold this hypothesis, that doesn't mean it has been proven. Micro-evolution (adaptive changes within species) is observable fact, but macro-evolution from single cells to humans has never been directly observed. Christians need not doubt the Creator's existence because of the evolutionary hypothesis."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "历史上宗教迫害了科学家（如伽利略），证明宗教反对科学。",
        "objection_en": "Religion historically persecuted scientists (like Galileo), proving religion opposes science.",
        "response_zh": "伽利略事件常被过度简化。伽利略本人是虔诚的基督徒，他的许多支持者是教会人士。冲突更多是政治和个人的，而非科学与信仰的本质冲突。更重要的事实是：现代科学的大多数奠基人都是基督徒——牛顿、法拉第、麦克斯韦、巴斯德、开普勒等。他们正是因为信仰一位理性的创造者，才相信自然界有可被发现的规律。",
        "response_en": "The Galileo affair is often oversimplified. Galileo himself was a devout Christian, and many of his supporters were churchmen. The conflict was more political and personal than an essential conflict between science and faith. More importantly, most founders of modern science were Christians — Newton, Faraday, Maxwell, Pasteur, Kepler, etc. Their belief in a rational Creator gave them confidence that nature had discoverable laws."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "奇迹违反自然规律，科学时代不能相信奇迹。",
        "objection_en": "Miracles violate natural laws; we can't believe in miracles in a scientific age.",
        "response_zh": "这混淆了自然规律与形而上学假设。自然规律描述的是在没有外力干预时自然界的正常运作方式。如果存在一位创造了自然规律的上帝，祂当然有能力和权利在特殊情况下作出例外。C.S. Lewis指出：奇迹不是违反自然规律，而是自然规律的创立者加入了一个新的因素。问题的关键不是“奇迹可能吗？“而是“上帝存在吗？“——如果上帝存在，奇迹就完全可能。",
        "response_en": "This confuses natural laws with metaphysical assumptions. Natural laws describe how nature normally operates without outside intervention. If a God who created natural laws exists, He certainly has the ability and right to make exceptions. C.S. Lewis noted: miracles aren't violations of natural law but the Lawgiver introducing a new factor. The key question isn't 'Are miracles possible?' but 'Does God exist?' — if God exists, miracles are entirely possible."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "科学已经解释了一切，不需要上帝",
        "objection_en": "Science has explained everything; we don't need God",
        "response_zh": "科学解释的是自然过程的'怎样'（how），而非'为什么'（why）。科学可以描述大爆炸的过程，但无法回答为什么会有大爆炸。方法论自然主义（科学方法排除超自然解释）不等于本体论自然主义（超自然不存在）。许多开创性科学家——牛顿、法拉第、麦克斯韦、普朗克——都是虔诚的信徒。",
        "response_en": "Science explains the 'how' of natural processes, not the 'why.' It can describe the Big Bang process but cannot answer why there is a Big Bang at all. Methodological naturalism (excluding supernatural in scientific method) does not equal ontological naturalism (the supernatural doesn't exist). Many pioneering scientists—Newton, Faraday, Maxwell, Planck—were devout believers."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "进化论已经推翻了创造论",
        "objection_en": "Evolution has disproved creationism",
        "response_zh": "进化论描述的是生物多样性的机制，而非宇宙和生命的终极起源。即使完全接受进化论，仍需要解释：（1）为什么存在一个能产生进化的宇宙？（2）为什么自然规律如此精确地允许生命出现？（3）生命最初如何从无机物中产生？许多严肃的科学家同时接受进化论和上帝的存在。",
        "response_en": "Evolution describes the mechanism of biodiversity, not the ultimate origin of the universe and life. Even fully accepting evolution, one must still explain: (1) Why does a universe capable of evolution exist? (2) Why are natural laws precisely tuned for life? (3) How did life first arise from non-living matter? Many serious scientists accept both evolution and God's existence."
      }
