  {
    "id": "sec-002",
    "target_worldview": "secularism",
    "topic_zh": "宗教多元主义：所有宗教都通向同一个上帝吗？",
    "topic_en": "Religious Pluralism: Do All Religions Lead to the Same God?",
    "core_argument_zh": "多元主义声称\"所有宗教最终都指向同一个终极实在\"，但仔细考察会发现各大宗教在最核心的问题上有不可调和的矛盾。基督教说上帝是有位格的三位一体；佛教说终极实在是无我和空性；印度教的不二论说最终只有梵我一如。这些不是同一真理的不同表达——它们是相互排斥的真理声称。\n\n约翰·希克（John Hick）的多元主义理论认为各宗教都是对同一\"真实者\"（the Real）的不同回应。但这个理论自身也是一种排他性声称——它声称自己对宗教本质的理解优于每个宗教自身的理解。这是一种\"超级傲慢\"——你比基督徒更了解基督教，比穆斯林更了解伊斯兰教。\n\n\"盲人摸象\"的比喻常被用来支持多元主义，但这个比喻实际上预设了有一个全知的视角（讲故事的人能看到完整的大象）。谁站在这个全知的位置上？基督教的声称恰恰是上帝在基督里主动启示了完整的真理——不是人类在黑暗中摸索，而是光照进了黑暗中。\n\n真正尊重各宗教的态度不是说\"你们其实都是一样的\"（这是不尊重每个宗教的独特宣称），而是认真对待它们的差异，真诚地寻求哪个的真理声称最有证据支持。C.S.路易斯说得好：基督教不是说其他宗教完全错误——它说基督教是完整的真理，而其他宗教包含部分真理。",
    "core_argument_en": "Pluralism claims 'all religions ultimately point to the same reality,' but careful examination reveals irreconcilable contradictions on core questions. Christianity says God is a personal Trinity; Buddhism says ultimate reality is no-self and emptiness; Hinduism's Advaita says only Brahman-Atman unity exists. These aren't different expressions of the same truth — they're mutually exclusive claims.\n\nJohn Hick's pluralism claims all religions respond differently to the same 'Real.' But this is itself an exclusivist claim — asserting a better understanding of religion's nature than each religion has of itself. This is 'super-arrogance' — claiming to understand Christianity better than Christians, Islam better than Muslims.\n\nThe 'blind men and elephant' parable often supports pluralism, but actually presupposes an omniscient perspective (the storyteller sees the whole elephant). Who occupies that position? Christianity's claim is precisely that God in Christ actively revealed the complete truth — not humans groping in darkness, but light shining into darkness.\n\nTrue respect for religions isn't saying 'you're all the same' (which disrespects each religion's unique claims) but taking their differences seriously and sincerely seeking which truth claims have the strongest evidence. C.S. Lewis said it well: Christianity doesn't say other religions are completely wrong — it says Christianity is the complete truth, while other religions contain partial truths.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "说只有一种宗教是对的太傲慢了。",
        "objection_en": "It's arrogant to claim only one religion is true.",
        "response_zh": "说别人“傲慢“本身也是一个真理主张——你在主张自己的立场（多元主义）比排他主义更正确。每个人都有真理主张，包括多元主义者。真正的问题不是“谁傲慢“，而是“什么是真的“。此外，如果基督教是真的——上帝亲自来到世上死在十字架上来拯救人——那最傲慢的回应不是相信它，而是对这样伟大的爱说“没必要“。正如Keller所说，认为自己不需要被拯救才是最深的傲慢。",
        "response_en": "Calling someone 'arrogant' is itself a truth claim — you're asserting your position (pluralism) is more correct than exclusivism. Everyone makes truth claims, including pluralists. The real question isn't 'Who's arrogant?' but 'What's true?' Furthermore, if Christianity is true — God personally came to die on the Cross to save humanity — the most arrogant response isn't believing it but telling such great love 'That's unnecessary.' As Keller notes, thinking you don't need saving is the deepest arrogance."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "瞎子摸象的故事不是说明每种宗教只看到了真理的一部分吗？",
        "objection_en": "Doesn't the parable of the blind men and the elephant show each religion sees only part of the truth?",
        "response_zh": "这个类比有一个致命缺陷：讲这个故事的人自认为能看到整头大象——他们自称拥有所有瞎子都没有的全面视角。这恰恰是他们指责排他主义者做的事！此外，基督教的独特之处不是人在摸索上帝，而是上帝主动向人启示自己。不是瞎子在猜大象，而是大象走过来介绍自己。道成肉身意味着上帝不再是我们猜测的对象——祂进入了我们的世界。",
        "response_en": "This analogy has a fatal flaw: the person telling the story claims to see the whole elephant — claiming a comprehensive perspective none of the blind men have. That's exactly what they accuse exclusivists of doing! Moreover, Christianity's uniqueness isn't humans groping for God but God actively revealing Himself to us. The blind men aren't guessing about the elephant — the elephant walks over and introduces Himself. The Incarnation means God is no longer an object of our speculation — He entered our world."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "宗教排他性导致冲突和暴力。",
        "objection_en": "Religious exclusivism leads to conflict and violence.",
        "response_zh": "这混淆了逻辑排他性和行为上的不宽容。相信自己的信仰是真的并不意味着要对持不同信仰的人不好。恰恰相反，耶稣教导我们要爱仇敌（马太福音5:44）。事实上，每种世界观——包括世俗主义——都有排他性真理主张。世俗主义声称宗教排他性是“坏的“——这本身就是一个排他性立场。关键是我们如何对待不同意见的人，而非我们是否持有真理主张。",
        "response_en": "This confuses logical exclusivity with behavioral intolerance. Believing your faith is true doesn't mean treating people of other faiths badly. On the contrary, Jesus teaches us to love our enemies (Matthew 5:44). In fact, every worldview — including secularism — makes exclusive truth claims. Secularism's claim that religious exclusivism is 'bad' is itself an exclusive position. What matters is how we treat those who disagree, not whether we hold truth claims."
      }
    ],
