    "id": "sec-003",
    "target_worldview": "secularism",
    "topic_zh": "基督教是压迫性的吗？——回应社会公义的批评",
    "topic_en": "Is Christianity Oppressive? — Responding to Social Justice Critiques",
    "core_argument_zh": "基督教被指控为\"排他性的\"和\"不宽容的\"，但这种批评本身也是排他性的——它排除了所有认为有绝对真理的世界观。说\"不应该声称自己是唯一的真理\"本身就是一个关于真理的排他性声称。所有严肃的世界观都是\"排他性的\"，包括世俗主义和多元主义。\n\n真正的问题不是一个信仰是否具有排他性，而是它是否为真。如果耶稣真的是上帝道成肉身，真的从死里复活了，那么他说\"我就是道路、真理、生命\"（约翰福音14:6）就不是傲慢——而是事实的陈述。基督教的\"排他性\"不是来自基督徒的傲慢，而是来自基督本人的宣告。\n\n此外，基督教在\"排他性\"的教义中包含了极其\"包容性\"的邀请：救恩对所有人开放，不分种族、性别、社会地位或过去的罪行。\"上帝不偏待人\"（使徒行传10:34）。启示录7:9描绘了来自\"各国、各族、各民、各方\"的人在天上的异象。基督教是历史上最跨文化、最多元种族的信仰运动。\n\n宽容的真正含义不是\"认为所有观点都同样正确\"（这是冷漠），而是\"在不同意的情况下仍然尊重和爱对方\"。基督教教导我们爱仇敌（马太福音5:44）、尊重每个人的尊严——这才是真正的宽容。",
    "core_argument_en": "Christianity is accused of being 'exclusive' and 'intolerant,' but this criticism is itself exclusive — it excludes all worldviews claiming absolute truth. Saying 'no one should claim to have the only truth' is itself an exclusive truth claim. All serious worldviews are 'exclusive,' including secularism and pluralism.\n\nThe real question isn't whether a faith is exclusive but whether it's true. If Jesus truly is God incarnate who truly rose from the dead, then His claim 'I am the way, the truth, and the life' (John 14:6) isn't arrogance — it's a factual statement. Christianity's 'exclusivity' comes not from Christian arrogance but from Christ's own declarations.\n\nMoreover, Christianity's 'exclusive' doctrine contains an extremely 'inclusive' invitation: salvation is open to all, regardless of race, gender, social status, or past sins. 'God shows no partiality' (Acts 10:34). Revelation 7:9 envisions people from 'every nation, tribe, people, and language' in heaven. Christianity is history's most cross-cultural, multi-ethnic faith movement.\n\nTrue tolerance doesn't mean 'considering all views equally correct' (that's indifference) but 'respecting and loving others while disagreeing.' Christianity teaches loving enemies (Matthew 5:44) and respecting every person's dignity — this is genuine tolerance.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "基督教历史上有十字军东征、宗教裁判所等暴行。",
        "objection_en": "Christianity has a history of violence — Crusades, Inquisition, etc.",
        "response_zh": "这些暴行确实发生了，基督徒应当诚实承认并忏悔。但这些行为违背了耶稣的教导（“收刀入鞘“，马太福音26:52），不能代表基督教本身。判断一种信仰应该看其核心教导，而非其信徒的失败。此外，20世纪无神论政权（斯大林、毛泽东、波尔布特）造成的死亡远超所有宗教战争的总和。暴力不是宗教的专利——它是人类堕落本性的结果。",
        "response_en": "These atrocities did happen, and Christians should honestly acknowledge and repent of them. But these acts violated Jesus' teaching ('Put your sword back,' Matthew 26:52) and don't represent Christianity itself. A faith should be judged by its core teachings, not its followers' failures. Furthermore, 20th-century atheist regimes (Stalin, Mao, Pol Pot) caused more deaths than all religious wars combined. Violence isn't unique to religion — it's a consequence of fallen human nature."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "基督教对性少数群体（LGBTQ+）的立场是歧视。",
        "objection_en": "Christianity's position on LGBTQ+ issues is discriminatory.",
        "response_zh": "基督教对性伦理的立场来自于对人类整全flourishing的愿景——上帝设计婚姻为一男一女终身之约，是为了人类的好处。这不是出于恐惧或仇恨，而是出于对上帝创造秩序的信念。同时，圣经教导每个人——无论性取向如何——都是按上帝形象造的，拥有不可侵犯的尊严。基督徒被呼召爱每一个人，即使在道德判断上有分歧。真正的爱不是无条件地认同一切，而是忠实地说真话并始终关心对方的好处。",
        "response_en": "Christianity's sexual ethic comes from a vision of holistic human flourishing — God designed marriage as a lifelong covenant between man and woman for humanity's good. This stems not from fear or hatred but from conviction about God's created order. At the same time, Scripture teaches every person — regardless of sexual orientation — is made in God's image with inviolable dignity. Christians are called to love everyone, even amid moral disagreements. True love isn't unconditional affirmation of everything but faithfully speaking truth while always seeking the other's good."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "基督教对女性的态度一直是压迫性的。",
        "objection_en": "Christianity has always been oppressive toward women.",
        "response_zh": "这是对历史的严重简化。耶稣在第一世纪极端父权制的文化中以革命性的方式对待女性：他公开与女性交谈（约翰福音4章）、有女性门徒（路加福音8:1-3）、让女性成为复活的首批见证人（在当时文化中女性证词不被法庭接受）。早期教会中女性担任重要角色：百基拉是教师，非比是执事。历史上，基督教推动了女性教育、妇女医院的建立和反对杀婴陋习。圣经教导丈夫要'爱妻子，正如基督爱教会'（以弗所书5:25），这在古代世界是革命性的要求——要求丈夫为妻子牺牲自己。",
        "response_en": "This seriously oversimplifies history. Jesus treated women revolutionarily within first-century patriarchal culture: He spoke publicly with women (John 4), had female disciples (Luke 8:1-3), and made women the first resurrection witnesses (when women's testimony was inadmissible in court). Early church women held important roles: Priscilla was a teacher, Phoebe a deacon. Historically, Christianity drove women's education, women's hospitals, and opposition to infanticide. Scripture teaches husbands to 'love your wives as Christ loved the church' (Ephesians 5:25) — a revolutionary demand in the ancient world, requiring husbands to sacrifice themselves for their wives."
      }
