    "id": "islam-004",
    "target_worldview": "islam",
    "topic_zh": "十字架受难：历史确定性对比古兰经的否认",
    "topic_en": "The Crucifixion: Historical Certainty vs the Quran's Denial",
    "core_argument_zh": "古兰经4:157声称耶稣并未真正被钉十字架（\"他们没有杀死他，也没有把他钉十字架，只是事情被弄得对他们有些模糊\"），但这一主张与古代历史记录严重矛盾。罗马历史学家塔西佗（约115年）记载基督在本丢·彼拉多手下受难；犹太历史学家约瑟夫斯（约93年）提到耶稣被彼拉多定罪钉十字架；犹太法典也提及耶稣的死刑。\n\n在学术界，耶稣死于十字架几乎是无可争议的历史事实。即使是最怀疑的学者约翰·多米尼克·克罗桑也说：\"耶稣被钉十字架在历史确定性方面几乎与任何事情一样确定。\"否认十字架的立场不是来自历史证据，而是来自古兰经600年后的神学重构。\n\n古兰经的\"替身论\"——即有人被变成耶稣的样子替他死——面临严重的神学和哲学困难：如果上帝使一个无辜者被误认为耶稣而受死，这意味着上帝主动制造了一个历史骗局，误导了数十亿人长达600年。这与上帝的诚实本性直接矛盾。\n\n基督教的十字架不仅有历史证据，更有深刻的神学意义：\"上帝在基督里叫世人与自己和好\"（哥林多后书5:19）。十字架不是失败而是胜利——是上帝之爱和公义的最高彰显。",
    "core_argument_en": "Quran 4:157 claims Jesus was not truly crucified ('they did not kill him, nor did they crucify him, but it appeared so to them'), but this contradicts ancient historical records. Roman historian Tacitus (~115 AD) records Christ suffering under Pontius Pilate; Jewish historian Josephus (~93 AD) mentions Jesus being condemned to crucifixion by Pilate; the Talmud also references Jesus' execution.\n\nAcademically, Jesus' death by crucifixion is virtually undisputed historical fact. Even the most skeptical scholar John Dominic Crossan says: 'Jesus' death by crucifixion is as historically certain as anything can be.' The denial comes not from historical evidence but from the Quran's theological reconstruction 600 years later.\n\nThe Quran's 'substitution theory' — someone being made to look like Jesus and dying in his place — faces severe theological and philosophical difficulties: if God caused an innocent person to be mistaken for Jesus and die, God actively created a historical deception misleading billions for 600 years. This directly contradicts God's truthful nature.\n\nThe Christian Cross has both historical evidence and profound theological meaning: 'God was reconciling the world to himself in Christ' (2 Corinthians 5:19). The Cross is not defeat but victory — the supreme display of God's love and justice.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "也许是犹大或其他人被变成耶稣的样子替他受死。",
        "objection_en": "Perhaps Judas or someone else was made to look like Jesus and died in his place.",
