        "objection_zh": "穆斯林也爱耶稣，古兰经对耶稣的评价很高。",
        "objection_en": "Muslims also love Jesus; the Quran speaks very highly of him.",
        "response_zh": "古兰经确实尊重耶稣为先知，记载了他的童女降生和行神迹。但“尊重”不等于“准确”。如果耶稣确实是上帝的儿子（如他自己所宣称的），那么将他降格为仅仅一位先知不是尊重，而是对他身份的根本否认。这就像有人说“我很尊重林肯——我认为他是加拿大一位优秀的小学教师”。称赞的话不能弥补身份的根本错误。",
        "response_en": "The Quran does honor Jesus as a prophet and records his virgin birth and miracles. But 'honor' does not equal 'accuracy.' If Jesus truly is the Son of God (as he himself claimed), then reducing him to merely a prophet is not honor but a fundamental denial of his identity. This is like saying 'I deeply respect Lincoln — I consider him an excellent elementary school teacher in Canada.' Complimentary words cannot compensate for a fundamental error about identity."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶稣的神性是保罗发明的，不是耶稣自己教导的。",
        "objection_en": "Jesus' deity was invented by Paul, not taught by Jesus himself.",
        "response_zh": "这个说法站不住脚。首先，在保罗之前的早期信经（如腓立比书2:6-11、哥林多前书8:6）已经表达了对耶稣神性的信仰——这些信经的形成时间可以追溯到教会最早期。其次，耶稣自己宣称有赦罪的权柄（马可福音2:5-7，犹太人认为只有上帝能赦罪）、接受敬拜（马太福音28:9）、使用上帝的自称“我是”（约翰福音8:58，对应出埃及记3:14）。犹太领袖要杀他恰恰是因为他“将自己当作上帝”（约翰福音5:18, 10:33）。",
        "response_en": "This claim does not hold. First, pre-Pauline creeds (such as Philippians 2:6-11, 1 Corinthians 8:6) already express faith in Jesus' deity — these creeds date to the earliest period of the church, before Paul's writings. Second, Jesus himself claimed authority to forgive sins (Mark 2:5-7 — Jews believed only God could forgive sins), accepted worship (Matthew 28:9), and used God's self-designation 'I AM' (John 8:58, echoing Exodus 3:14). The Jewish leaders sought to kill him precisely because he 'made himself equal with God' (John 5:18, 10:33)."
