        "response_en": "If all versions were identical, why was burning necessary? The very need for unification presupposes differences. Islamic tradition itself records these differences: Ibn Masud (one of Muhammad's recommended Quran authorities) refused to accept Uthman's version — his version lacked two surahs. Moreover, early Islamic sources record Aisha (Muhammad's wife) claiming certain verses were lost. We are not attacking the Quran but pointing out that if Muslims' criticisms of the Bible are applied equally to the Quran, the problems are greater."
