        "response_en": "Christian failures actually confirm a core Christian doctrine: humans are sinners, imperfect even after believing in God. But these historical tragedies occurred not because of following Christian teaching but precisely because of violating it. By contrast, the 20th century's largest human rights catastrophes (Stalin's USSR, Mao's China, Pol Pot's Cambodia) all occurred under explicitly atheist regimes — when the belief that 'humans are made in God's image' is removed, nothing prevents the state from treating people as disposable tools. The abolition movement, civil rights movement, and founding of modern hospitals and universities all root in the Christian vision of human rights."
