        "objection_en": "Worldview analysis oversimplifies complex philosophical issues",
        "response_zh": "实际上，世界观分析法能够处理哲学问题的全部复杂性，因为它承认所有具体的哲学争议都根植于更深层的形而上学和认识论预设。传统护教学往往在表面现象层面争论，而忽略了背后的根本假设。世界观分析法要求我们深入到最基础的层面——关于实在的本质、知识的可能性、价值的来源等根本问题。这种方法不是简化，而是系统化。它要求护教者掌握哲学史、科学哲学、认识论等多个领域的知识。范泰尔本人就是深刻的哲学家，他对康德、黑格尔等思想家的分析极为精细。世界观分析法的优势在于它能够揭示各种表面不同的理论背后共同的无神论预设，从而进行更有效的根本性批判。",
        "response_en": "In fact, the worldview analysis method can handle the full complexity of philosophical issues because it recognizes that all specific philosophical disputes are rooted in deeper metaphysical and epistemological presuppositions. Traditional apologetics often argues at the level of surface phenomena while ignoring the underlying fundamental assumptions. Worldview analysis requires us to go to the most foundational level—fundamental questions about the nature of reality, the possibility of knowledge, and the source of values. This method is not simplification but systematization. It requires the apologist to master knowledge across multiple fields including the history of philosophy, philosophy of science, and epistemology. Van Til himself was a profound philosopher whose analyses of thinkers like Kant and Hegel were extremely nuanced. The advantage of worldview analysis lies in its ability to reveal the common atheistic presuppositions behind various superficially different theories, enabling more effective fundamental critique."
