        "response_zh": "世界观分析法实际上促进了更深层次的学术交流，因为它诚实地承认了思想背后的根本预设和价值承诺。隐藏或否认世界观差异才是真正阻碍对话的因素。当我们假装可以采取中性立场时，我们实际上是在强加自己的世界观，同时否认这种强加的存在。世界观分析法要求双方都诚实地承认自己的预设，这为更坦诚的对话创造了条件。约翰·弗雷姆指出，这种方法并不排斥谦卑、尊重和爱心。认识到世界观差异不等于敌视对方，而是理解对话的真正本质。最深刻的学术对话往往发生在世界观层面，因为这是思想最根本的分歧所在。",
        "response_en": "The worldview analysis method actually promotes deeper academic exchange because it honestly acknowledges the fundamental presuppositions and value commitments underlying thought. Concealing or denying worldview differences is what truly hinders dialogue. When we pretend that a neutral standpoint is possible, we are actually imposing our own worldview while denying that this imposition exists. Worldview analysis requires both parties to honestly acknowledge their presuppositions, creating conditions for more candid dialogue. John Frame points out that this method does not preclude humility, respect, and love. Recognizing worldview differences does not mean being hostile toward the other party but rather understanding the true nature of dialogue. The most profound academic conversations often occur at the worldview level because that is where the most fundamental divergences of thought lie."
