      {
        "objection_zh": "即使前设护教学不是循环的，它仍然是武断的，因为它拒绝接受中性证据",
        "objection_en": "Even if presuppositional apologetics isn't circular, it is still arbitrary because it refuses to accept neutral evidence",
        "response_zh": "前设护教学不是拒绝证据，而是坚持所有证据都必须在某个解释框架内被理解。没有「原始事实」或「中性数据」这样的东西——所有的观察和推理都是理论负载的(theory-laden)。范泰尔从未否认自然启示或历史证据的重要性，他只是坚持这些证据必须在正确的认识论框架内才能得到正确解释。例如，复活的历史证据在基督教框架内是神迹的证明，但在自然主义框架内必须被重新解释为幻觉、传说或欺骗。问题不在于证据本身，而在于解释证据的世界观预设。前设护教学的「武断」实际上是对认识论诚实性的坚持——我们必须承认我们的基本承诺，而不是假装我们可以采取中性立场。这种诚实使真正的对话成为可能。",
        "response_en": "Presuppositional apologetics does not reject evidence but insists that all evidence must be understood within some interpretive framework. There is no such thing as 'raw facts' or 'neutral data'—all observation and reasoning is theory-laden. Van Til never denied the importance of natural revelation or historical evidence; he simply insisted that this evidence can only be correctly interpreted within the right epistemological framework. For example, the historical evidence for the resurrection is, within the Christian framework, proof of a miracle, but within the naturalistic framework it must be reinterpreted as hallucination, legend, or deception. The issue is not the evidence itself but the worldview presuppositions used to interpret it. Presuppositionalism's supposed 'dogmatism' is actually an insistence on epistemological honesty—we must acknowledge our basic commitments rather than pretending we can adopt a neutral stance. This honesty makes genuine dialogue possible."
