        "response_zh": "融合式护教学不是方法论上的混乱，而是对护教学复杂性的成熟认识。奥利芬特的融合方法基于一个重要的神学洞察：圣经本身既使用先验论证(如诗篇14:1「愚顽人心里说：没有神」)，也使用经验论证(如以赛亚书的历史预言应验)。问题不在于选择一种方法排除另一种，而在于如何正确地整合它们。融合方法的关键原则是：始终以承认神的权威为出发点，然后在这个基础上展示证据如何确证圣经真理。这避免了古典护教学的方法论错误(假设堕落理性的自主性)，同时充分利用了神在自然界和历史中的启示。不同的听众和情境可能需要强调不同的方面，但基础的前设承诺应该始终保持一致。",
        "response_en": "Integrative apologetics is not methodological confusion but a mature recognition of apologetics' complexity. Oliphint's integrative method is based on an important theological insight: Scripture itself uses both transcendental arguments (e.g., Psalm 14:1, 'The fool says in his heart, \"There is no God\"') and empirical arguments (e.g., Isaiah's fulfilled historical prophecies). The issue is not choosing one method to the exclusion of the other, but how to properly integrate them. The key principle of the integrative method is: always start by acknowledging God's authority, then on that basis show how evidence confirms biblical truth. This avoids the methodological error of classical apologetics (assuming fallen reason's autonomy) while fully utilizing God's revelation in nature and history. Different audiences and contexts may call for emphasis on different aspects, but the foundational presuppositional commitment should always remain consistent."
