        "response_zh": "十字军的历史背景远比流行叙事复杂。第一次十字军东征（1096年）是对伊斯兰扩张数百年后的军事回应，当时拜占庭帝国请求西方援助。这并不意味着十字军的一切行为都合理——屠杀平民确实是对基督教导的严重背叛。至于宗教裁判所，亨利·卡门（Henry Kamen）的研究表明，西班牙宗教裁判所在350年间处决约3000-5000人，远少于许多世俗政权单年的杀戮。关键是：这些暴力行为违背了基督的教导，而非遵从。我们应当以基督本人的教导——而非人的失败——来评判基督教。",
        "response_en": "The Crusades' historical context is far more complex than the popular narrative. The First Crusade (1096) was a military response to centuries of Islamic expansion, with the Byzantine Empire requesting Western aid. This doesn't justify all Crusader actions—massacres of civilians were grave betrayals of Christ's teaching. As for the Inquisition, Henry Kamen's research shows the Spanish Inquisition executed approximately 3,000-5,000 people over 350 years, far fewer than many secular regimes killed in a single year. The key point: these violent acts contradicted Christ's teaching, not followed it. We should judge Christianity by Christ's own teaching, not by human failures."
