        "response_en": "First, lumping all religions together is unreasonable—different religions have fundamentally different core teachings. Christianity's founder Jesus said 'Put your sword back' (Matthew 26:52) and went to the cross rather than waging war. Second, even within Islam, interpretation of violent texts is hotly debated. Third, much so-called 'religious' terrorism is actually driven by geopolitics, economic inequality, and colonial legacies. Robert Pape's study of suicide attacks found their primary motivation was opposition to foreign military occupation, not religious belief."
