        "response_zh": "福音恰恰不是「一样对待」——它是超越公平的恩典。如果上帝按公平对待每个人，那所有人都会被定罪，因为没有人完全符合上帝的标准。恩典的意思是：我们不配得到的好处，上帝白白赐给我们。这就像一群溺水的人——有的离岸近，有的离岸远，但都在溺水。差别不在于你游得多好，而在于是否接受救生圈。而且，圣经确实教导程度的区别：在审判中有不同程度的赏赐和惩罚（路加福音12:47-48），但进入天堂的唯一基础是基督的义，而非我们自己的功德。",
        "response_en": "The Gospel is precisely not 'treating everyone the same'—it's grace that transcends fairness. If God treated everyone fairly, all would be condemned, since no one fully meets God's standard. Grace means: undeserved blessings God gives freely. It's like drowning people—some closer to shore, some farther, but all drowning. The difference isn't how well you swim, but whether you accept the life preserver. Moreover, the Bible does teach degrees of difference: varying rewards and punishments at judgment (Luke 12:47-48), but the sole basis for entering heaven is Christ's righteousness, not our own merit."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "很多基督徒的品行还不如不信的人，这不是说明信仰无用吗？",
        "objection_en": "Many Christians behave worse than non-believers. Doesn't that prove faith is useless?",
        "response_zh": "基督徒行为的失败恰恰证明了福音的要点：基督徒不是「好人的俱乐部」，而是「认识到自己需要恩典的罪人的团契」。教会是医院，不是博物馆。有些基督徒的虚伪确实令人失望，但这正说明了为什么我们不能靠自己的「好」来得救——即使信了主的人仍在「成圣」的过程中挣扎。C.S.路易斯指出：正确的比较不是基督徒和非基督徒之间的比较，而是同一个人信主前后的比较。信仰的果效是真实的改变，尽管这改变是渐进的、不完美的。",
        "response_en": "Christians' moral failures actually prove the Gospel's point: Christians are not a 'club for good people' but a 'fellowship of sinners who recognize their need for grace.' The church is a hospital, not a museum. Some Christians' hypocrisy is genuinely disappointing, but this demonstrates precisely why we cannot be saved by our own 'goodness'—even believers still struggle in the process of 'sanctification.' C.S. Lewis pointed out: the proper comparison isn't between Christians and non-Christians, but the same person before and after faith. Faith's fruit is real transformation, even though it's gradual and imperfect."
