        "response_en": "'God of the gaps' is indeed a poor argument, but Christianity's core arguments don't rely on it. The cosmological, design, and moral arguments aren't based on gaps science can't explain, but on what we already know (the universe began, fine-tuning, objective morality exists) to infer the best explanation. Newton studied gravity not to replace God but to understand God's created order. Discovering laws deepens awe at the Creator's wisdom rather than eliminating the need for Him."
