        "response_zh": "这个论证本身就是自我反驳的：「只有可科学检验的信念才值得相信」这一命题本身是无法被科学检验的——它是一个哲学立场，不是科学结论。这种立场被称为「科学主义」（scientism），连许多无神论哲学家都拒绝它。数学真理、逻辑规律、伦理判断、美学经验、其他心灵的存在——这些都无法被科学方法证实，但我们理性地相信它们。科学是认识实在的重要工具之一，但不是唯一工具。",
        "response_en": "This argument is self-refuting: the claim 'only scientifically testable beliefs are worth believing' is itself not scientifically testable—it's a philosophical position, not a scientific conclusion. This position, called 'scientism,' is rejected even by many atheist philosophers. Mathematical truths, logical laws, ethical judgments, aesthetic experience, the existence of other minds—none can be verified by the scientific method, yet we rationally believe them. Science is an important tool for knowing reality, but not the only one."
