        "objection_zh": "那些从未听过福音的人怎么办？上帝会因为地理位置而定人的罪吗？",
        "objection_en": "What about people who never heard the Gospel? Would God condemn someone based on geography?",
        "response_zh": "这是一个严肃且值得认真对待的问题。圣经给出几个重要的原则：第一，上帝的公义是完美的——「审判全地的主岂不行公义吗？」（创世记18:25）。第二，罗马书1:20教导所有人都通过创造认识到上帝的存在，因此没有人是完全无知的。第三，罗马书2:14-15说上帝的律法写在人心里——人凭良知就知道自己是有罪的。第四，圣经留下了盼望的空间：上帝可能有我们不知道的施恩方式。但圣经清楚的是：我们所确知的拯救之路是耶稣基督，因此传福音的紧迫性不减。第五，这一问题恰恰应该激励我们更积极地传福音——如果有人因未听闻福音而面对审判，那传播福音就是最重要的使命。",
        "response_en": "This is a serious question deserving careful treatment. Scripture provides several key principles: First, God's justice is perfect—'Will not the Judge of all the earth do right?' (Genesis 18:25). Second, Romans 1:20 teaches all people recognize God's existence through creation, so no one is completely ignorant. Third, Romans 2:14-15 says God's law is written on human hearts—people know through conscience they are sinful. Fourth, Scripture leaves room for hope: God may have ways of extending grace we don't know about. But Scripture is clear that the salvation path we know with certainty is Jesus Christ, so the urgency of evangelism remains. Fifth, this question should motivate us to evangelize more actively—if people face judgment without hearing the Gospel, spreading it is our most important mission."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "宣称「只有一条路」是文化帝国主义，是西方殖民的遗产。",
        "objection_en": "Claiming 'only one way' is cultural imperialism, a legacy of Western colonialism.",
        "response_zh": "基督教不是西方宗教——它诞生于中东，最早的教会在耶路撒冷、安提阿和亚历山大。今天基督教增长最快的地区是非洲、亚洲和拉丁美洲，而非欧洲。拉民·桑内（Lamin Sanneh）——一位来自冈比亚的穆斯林改信者、耶鲁大学教授——在《信仰的翻译性》（Translating the Message）中论证：基督教独特地肯定每种文化和语言的价值，因为福音从一开始就是可翻译的。殖民主义是对基督教的扭曲利用，而非基督教的本质。而且，说「排他性真理主张是西方的」本身就是一种对非西方文化的傲慢假设——许多非西方文化传统同样有强烈的排他性真理主张。",
        "response_en": "Christianity isn't a Western religion—it was born in the Middle East, with the earliest churches in Jerusalem, Antioch, and Alexandria. Today Christianity grows fastest in Africa, Asia, and Latin America, not Europe. Lamin Sanneh—a Gambian Muslim convert and Yale professor—argues in Translating the Message that Christianity uniquely affirms every culture and language's value because the Gospel has been translatable from the beginning. Colonialism was a distortion of Christianity, not its essence. Moreover, claiming 'exclusive truth claims are Western' is itself a condescending assumption about non-Western cultures—many non-Western traditions also make strong exclusive truth claims."
      }
