        "response_zh": "自然选择是一个可观察的机制，可以解释物种内部的适应性变化（微观进化）。但自然选择能否驱动从简单到复杂的宏观进化？这仍然是一个远未解决的问题。迈克尔·比希（Michael Behe）在《达尔文的黑匣子》中提出「不可还原的复杂性」问题——某些生物系统需要多个部件同时运作才能有功能，渐进进化难以解释其起源。托马斯·内格尔（Thomas Nagel）——一位无神论哲学家——在《心灵与宇宙》中承认，纯粹唯物主义的进化假说无法充分解释意识、理性和价值的起源。斯蒂芬·迈耶（Stephen Meyer）在《细胞中的签名》中详细论证了DNA中功能性信息的起源无法通过自然选择解释。更根本地，自然选择只能在已有的遗传信息上进行筛选，无法解释新的复杂遗传信息的产生。",
        "response_en": "Natural selection is an observable mechanism that can explain adaptive changes within species (micro-evolution). But can natural selection drive macro-evolution from simple to complex? This remains far from settled. Michael Behe in Darwin's Black Box raises 'irreducible complexity'—some biological systems require multiple parts working simultaneously to function, making gradual evolution difficult to explain. Thomas Nagel—an atheist philosopher—admits in Mind and Cosmos that purely materialistic evolutionary hypothesis cannot adequately explain the origin of consciousness, reason, and values. Stephen Meyer in Signature in the Cell extensively argues that the origin of functional information in DNA cannot be explained through natural selection. More fundamentally, natural selection can only filter existing genetic information—it cannot explain the origin of new complex genetic information."
