    "core_argument_zh": "旧约圣经包含超过300处关于弥赛亚的预言，这些预言写成于耶稣降生前数百年至一千多年，却在耶稣基督身上精确应验。这一现象构成了圣经神圣启示性的有力证据。\n\n以赛亚书53章详细描述了受苦仆人的形象——他被藐视、被人厌弃、为我们的过犯受害、如羊被牵到宰杀之地。这段经文写于公元前700年左右，却与耶稣受难的细节惊人吻合。彼得·斯通纳（Peter Stoner）在《科学辩道》（Science Speaks）中用概率论计算，仅8条预言同时应验在一个人身上的概率为10的17次方分之一。而耶稣应验的预言远不止8条。\n\n弥迦书5:2预言弥赛亚生于伯利恒，撒迦利亚书11:12-13预言三十块银子的背叛价格，诗篇22篇描述了钉十字架的细节——而十字架刑罚在大卫写作时尚未被发明。死海古卷的发现（1947年）证实了这些旧约经文在耶稣之前已经存在，排除了「事后编造」的可能。学者迈克尔·布朗（Michael Brown）在其五卷本《回答犹太人的反对意见》中系统论证了弥赛亚预言的历史可靠性。\n\n批评者有时主张这些预言是模糊的、被后人重新诠释的。然而，许多预言包含极为具体的细节：出生地点、进入耶路撒冷的方式（骑驴驹）、被刺透、骨头不被打断、与财主同葬等。这些细节的精确性远超任何「事后附会」的解释力。正如F.F.布鲁斯（F.F. Bruce）所指出的，预言的应验模式是渐进的、有机的，不是机械的预测-实现关系，而是神在历史中展开救赎计划的明证。",
    "core_argument_en": "The Old Testament contains over 300 messianic prophecies written hundreds to over a thousand years before Jesus' birth, yet fulfilled precisely in His life. This phenomenon constitutes powerful evidence for the divine inspiration of Scripture.\n\nIsaiah 53 describes a suffering servant—despised, rejected, wounded for our transgressions, led like a lamb to slaughter. Written around 700 BC, it matches the details of Jesus' passion with stunning accuracy. Peter Stoner in Science Speaks calculated the probability of just 8 prophecies being fulfilled in one person at 1 in 10^17. Jesus fulfilled far more than eight.\n\nMicah 5:2 predicted the Messiah's birth in Bethlehem; Zechariah 11:12-13 foretold the betrayal price of thirty silver pieces; Psalm 22 described crucifixion details—before crucifixion was invented. The Dead Sea Scrolls (discovered 1947) confirmed these texts predated Jesus, eliminating the possibility of post-hoc fabrication. Scholar Michael Brown systematically demonstrates the historical reliability of messianic prophecy in his five-volume Answering Jewish Objections to Jesus.\n\nCritics sometimes claim these prophecies are vague or reinterpreted after the fact. However, many contain extremely specific details: birthplace, manner of entry into Jerusalem (on a donkey's colt), being pierced, bones unbroken, burial with the rich. As F.F. Bruce noted, the pattern of fulfillment is progressive and organic—not mechanical prediction-realization but evidence of God's redemptive plan unfolding through history.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "这些预言太模糊了，可以应用在任何人身上。",
        "objection_en": "These prophecies are too vague and could apply to anyone.",
        "response_zh": "许多弥赛亚预言包含极为具体的细节：出生在伯利恒（弥迦书5:2）、从埃及被召回（何西阿书11:1）、被三十块银子出卖（撒迦利亚书11:12）、骑驴驹进耶路撒冷（撒迦利亚书9:9）、手脚被刺透（诗篇22:16）、衣服被抓阄分（诗篇22:18）。这些细节的组合使得巧合的可能性在统计学上微乎其微。斯通纳的概率计算表明，即使仅选取8条预言，其同时应验的概率也低到令人震惊的程度。",
        "response_en": "Many messianic prophecies contain highly specific details: born in Bethlehem (Micah 5:2), called out of Egypt (Hosea 11:1), betrayed for thirty silver pieces (Zechariah 11:12), entering Jerusalem on a donkey's colt (Zechariah 9:9), hands and feet pierced (Psalm 22:16), garments divided by lot (Psalm 22:18). The combination makes coincidence statistically negligible. Stoner's probability calculations show that even selecting just 8 prophecies, the odds of simultaneous fulfillment are astronomically low."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶稣可能故意去'应验'这些预言。",
        "objection_en": "Jesus could have deliberately arranged to 'fulfill' these prophecies.",
        "response_zh": "许多预言涉及耶稣无法控制的事件：出生地点和家族谱系、犹大以三十块银子出卖他、罗马兵丁的具体行为（分衣服、不打断骨头）、十字架上的死亡方式。一个人无法策划自己的出生地、被谁出卖、或敌人如何对待自己的尸体。正如克雷格·布隆伯格（Craig Blomberg）所论证的，这些不可控因素使得「蓄意应验」的假设难以成立。",
        "response_en": "Many prophecies involve events beyond Jesus' control: birthplace and genealogy, Judas' betrayal for thirty silver pieces, Roman soldiers' specific actions (dividing garments, not breaking bones), the manner of crucifixion death. No one can orchestrate their own birthplace, who betrays them, or how enemies treat their body. As Craig Blomberg has argued, these uncontrollable factors make the 'deliberate fulfillment' hypothesis untenable."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "福音书作者可能编造故事来匹配旧约预言。",
        "objection_en": "Gospel writers may have fabricated stories to match Old Testament prophecies.",
        "response_zh": "首先，许多预言的应验细节可以被独立的非基督教来源验证，如耶稣的十字架死刑被罗马历史学家塔西佗和犹太史家约瑟夫斯所记载。其次，福音书记载了许多对早期教会「不方便」的细节（如门徒的软弱和背叛），这符合历史可靠性的标准。第三，如果编造故事，为什么选择许多当时犹太人并未普遍关注的「受苦弥赛亚」预言？当时流行的期待是政治性的得胜弥赛亚，而非受难的仆人。",
        "response_en": "First, many fulfillment details are independently verified by non-Christian sources—Jesus' crucifixion is attested by Tacitus and Josephus. Second, the Gospels record details embarrassing to the early church (disciples' failures and betrayals), meeting criteria of historical reliability. Third, if fabricating, why emphasize 'suffering Messiah' prophecies that Jews didn't commonly focus on? Popular expectation was a political, triumphant Messiah, not a suffering servant."
      }
    ],
