        "response_zh": "这是正确的区分，但考古学的意义在于建立圣经的可信度（credibility）。如果一份文献在可验证的历史细节上一再被证实是准确的，那么对其在不可直接验证的部分给予信任是合理的。正如法律中证人在可查证事实上的准确性会增加其整体可信度。考古学不「证明」神迹，但它排除了「圣经是后人编造的神话」这一常见假设。",
        "response_en": "This is a valid distinction, but archaeology's significance lies in establishing biblical credibility. If a document proves accurate on verifiable historical details, it's reasonable to extend trust to its unverifiable claims. Like legal testimony—a witness's accuracy on checkable facts increases overall credibility. Archaeology doesn't 'prove' miracles, but it eliminates the common assumption that 'the Bible is later fabricated mythology.'"
