        "objection_en": "Other ancient religious texts also contain some historical truths; that doesn't make them God's Word.",
        "response_zh": "圣经的独特之处不仅在于包含真实历史细节，而在于其历史记载的广度、深度和一致性都远超其他古代文献。圣经涵盖了两千年的历史跨度，涉及数十个文明和数百个可验证的细节，而考古学的印证率是其他古代文献无法比拟的。更重要的是，考古学印证只是圣经可靠性的一个维度，需要与预言的应验、内在一致性、改变生命的力量等多重证据一起综合考量。",
        "response_en": "The Bible's uniqueness lies not merely in containing some historical truths, but in the breadth, depth, and consistency of its historical record far exceeding other ancient documents. Spanning two thousand years of history, involving dozens of civilizations and hundreds of verifiable details, its archaeological confirmation rate is unmatched. Moreover, archaeological confirmation is just one dimension of biblical reliability, to be considered alongside fulfilled prophecy, internal consistency, and life-transforming power."
      }
