        "response_en": "Most alleged 'contradictions' fall into categories: (1) complementary perspectives on the same event (four Gospels recording Jesus' life from different angles); (2) surface differences from translation; (3) failure to account for genre (treating poetic language as scientific description). Greg Koukl in Tactics notes that genuine contradiction requires 'the same sense, same relationship, same time.' Upon careful analysis, nearly all alleged contradictions have reasonable harmonizations. See scr-006 for detailed discussion."
