        "response_en": "The Dead Sea Scrolls demonstrate extremely faithful Old Testament textual transmission, ruling out large-scale later editing. Moreover, biblical unity manifests not just in verbal coherence but in deep theological structure—the grand narrative of creation-fall-redemption runs throughout. Such structural unity far exceeds what simple editing could produce. Bruce Waltke in his Old Testament theology demonstrates this organic unity is intrinsic to the texts, not externally imposed."
