        "response_en": "The critical difference is the stringency of conditions. The Quran was written by one author over ~23 years—far less challenging for internal consistency. Biblical consistency was achieved across 40 authors, 1,500 years, three languages, and multiple cultures, making its unity argument fundamentally different. Furthermore, biblical consistency isn't merely the negative absence of contradiction but positively demonstrates a progressively unfolding redemptive plan—a phenomenon unique in the history of human literature."
