        "response_en": "This number needs proper context. First, 'variants' are counted such that if one word is spelled differently in one of 1,000 manuscripts, that counts as 1,000 variants. Second, the vast majority are: (1) spelling differences (e.g., different spellings of 'John'); (2) word order ('Christ Jesus' vs. 'Jesus Christ'); (3) obvious scribal slips. Less than 1% are meaningful, and none affect any core Christian doctrine. Daniel Wallace—a world-leading NT manuscript scholar—repeatedly emphasizes this. Even Ehrman himself acknowledges in academic works that the NT text is essentially reliable."
