        "response_en": "If this standard held, we'd have to reject all ancient history, since we possess virtually no original manuscripts of any ancient text. We don't have originals of Plato, Aristotle, or Caesar, yet no one doubts our knowledge of their works. Textual criticism's entire methodology reconstructs originals by comparing diverse manuscripts, and the NT's manuscript evidence enables far greater precision than any other ancient document. Metzger concluded that NT textual criticism yields results that are 'certain,' with reliability unmatched in classical literature."
