        "response_en": "This charge presupposes an absolute standard: 'Oppressing others is wrong.' Without objective moral truth, on what basis is oppression wrong? Christianity's truth claims are transmitted through persuasion and love, not coercion. Jesus himself relinquished power and went to the cross — the very antithesis of power logic."
