        "response_en": "The Turing Test measures behavioral imitation, not genuine understanding or consciousness. A program can perfectly simulate conversation with zero comprehension — as Searle's Chinese Room demonstrates. Appearing conscious is not being conscious. Turing himself acknowledged the test is not a sufficient condition for consciousness."
