    "topic_zh": "资本主义/马克思主义 vs 基督教经济观",
    "topic_en": "Capitalism/Marxism vs. Christian Economics",
    "core_argument_zh": "资本主义和马克思主义都提供了关于经济秩序的宏大叙事，但两者都有严重的神学盲点。不受约束的资本主义将市场绝对化，以利润最大化为最高目标，忽视了人的贪婪本性和对弱者的责任。马克思主义正确地看到了经济不公的问题，但其解决方案——消灭私有制、建立集体控制——忽视了人的罪性，在实践中导致了极权暴政。亚伯拉罕·凯柏（Abraham Kuyper）在其「领域主权」（sphere sovereignty）理论中论证，经济活动有其上帝赋予的正当领域，但不应僭越其他生活领域。迈克尔·诺瓦克（Michael Novak）在《民主资本主义的精神》中指出，健康的市场经济需要道德文化和政治自由的三重制衡。韦恩·格鲁登（Wayne Grudem）在《基督教与经济》中论证，圣经既肯定私有产权和勤劳致富的正当性，也严厉谴责剥削穷人和囤积财富。先知传统对经济不义的批判（阿摩司书5:11-12）与智慧文学对勤劳的肯定（箴言6:6-11）共同构成了一个平衡的经济伦理：财富是管家式的信托而非绝对的个人权利，公义与怜悯不可分割。",
    "core_argument_en": "Both capitalism and Marxism offer grand narratives about economic order, yet both have serious theological blind spots. Unconstrained capitalism absolutizes the market, maximizing profit as the highest goal while ignoring human greed and responsibility toward the vulnerable. Marxism rightly identifies economic injustice but its solution — abolishing private property for collective control — ignores human sinfulness, leading in practice to totalitarian tyranny. Abraham Kuyper's 'sphere sovereignty' theory argues that economic activity has its God-given legitimate sphere but must not encroach on other life domains. Michael Novak in 'The Spirit of Democratic Capitalism' notes healthy market economies need a three-way check of moral culture and political freedom. Wayne Grudem in 'Business for the Glory of God' argues Scripture affirms both private property and the legitimacy of wealth through diligence while strongly condemning exploitation of the poor and hoarding. The prophetic tradition's critique of economic injustice (Amos 5:11-12) together with wisdom literature's affirmation of diligence (Proverbs 6:6-11) forms a balanced economic ethic: wealth is stewardship trust, not absolute personal right; justice and mercy are inseparable.",
    "common_objections": [
      {
        "objection_zh": "耶稣不是反对富人吗？基督教应该支持社会主义。",
        "objection_en": "Didn't Jesus oppose the rich? Christianity should support socialism.",
        "response_zh": "耶稣反对的不是财富本身，而是对财富的偶像崇拜和对穷人的漠视。初代教会的「凡物公用」（徒2:44-45）是自愿的爱心行为，不是国家强制的再分配。圣经肯定私有产权（「不可偷盗」），也要求慷慨施舍。将基督教简单等同于任何现代经济意识形态都是对圣经的误读。",
        "response_en": "Jesus opposed not wealth itself but idolizing wealth and ignoring the poor. The early church's sharing (Acts 2:44-45) was voluntary charity, not state-enforced redistribution. Scripture affirms private property ('You shall not steal') while requiring generous giving. Equating Christianity with any modern economic ideology is a misreading of Scripture."
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "宗教不应干涉经济政策，政教要分离。",
        "objection_en": "Religion shouldn't interfere with economic policy; keep church and state separate.",
        "response_zh": "政教分离指的是教会不掌握政治权力，不意味着信仰不能影响公共道德判断。所有经济体系都建立在某种人论和价值观之上——这本身就是「宗教性」的。马克思主义自身就是一种准宗教的世俗救赎叙事。问题不是「是否有价值预设」，而是「哪种价值预设最接近现实」。",
        "response_en": "Separation of church and state means the church doesn't hold political power — not that faith cannot inform public moral judgments. All economic systems rest on some anthropology and values — which is itself 'religious.' Marxism is a quasi-religious secular salvation narrative. The question isn't 'whether value presuppositions exist' but 'which best approximates reality.'"
      },
      {
        "objection_zh": "基督教关注的是灵魂得救，不应该关心经济问题。",
        "objection_en": "Christianity is about saving souls, not economic concerns.",
        "response_zh": "这是一种错误的灵肉二元论。上帝关心的是整全的人——灵魂与身体。旧约律法中大量涉及经济公义的条例（禧年、拾穗律、禁止高利贷）表明上帝深切关注物质层面的公义。雅各布书2:15-16明确说，对饥饿之人只说「平平安安地去吧」而不给予帮助，这样的信仰是死的。",
        "response_en": "This reflects a false soul-body dualism. God cares about the whole person — soul and body. The Old Testament's extensive economic justice provisions (Jubilee, gleaning laws, prohibiting usury) show God's deep concern for material justice. James 2:15-16 states plainly that telling the hungry 'Go in peace' without helping makes faith dead."
      }
    ],
