    "core_argument_en": "The Unification Church (FFWPU) was founded by Korean Sun Myung Moon in 1954. Its core text 'Divine Principle' claims Jesus' mission failed through crucifixion — He achieved only 'spiritual salvation,' not 'physical salvation.' God therefore needed a 'Lord of the Second Advent' to complete redemption. Moon claimed to be this returning Christ, serving as 'True Parents' with wife Hak Ja Han, converting humanity from Satan's lineage to God's through 'Blessing' ceremonies. These teachings fundamentally deviate from orthodox Christianity. Richard Abanes in 'Cults, New Religions, and Your Family' analyzes these deviations. Scripture declares Christ's cross-work complete (John 19:30 'It is finished'; Heb 10:12-14) — there is no 'unfinished redemption.' Jesus Himself warned of false Christs (Matt 24:23-26) and stated His return would be a publicly visible cosmic event (Matt 24:27), not a secret birth in Korea. The 'blood lineage' doctrine has zero biblical support, and early 'pikareum' rituals (lineage transfer through sexual acts) are clearly heretical. Walter Martin's 'Kingdom of the Cults' classifies the Unification Church as a classic pseudo-Christian cult.",
