    "core_argument_zh": "新天地耶稣教证据帐幕圣殿（Shincheonji）由韩国人李万熙于1984年创立。该组织声称启示录中的预言已经在李万熙身上和新天地教会中「实际应验」——李万熙是启示录中「得胜者」（启2-3章），是唯一能揭开启示录封印的人，新天地的十四万四千人将组成末世的属灵以色列。这套解经体系的核心问题在于其极端的寓意化私意解经法。他们将启示录的每一个意象都指定为特定的现实对应，例如「太阳」代表某位牧师，「星星」代表某些信徒。然而正如戈登·费依（Gordon Fee）和道格拉斯·斯图尔特（Douglas Stuart）在《读经的艺术》中所强调的，释经的首要原则是尊重文本的原始语境和体裁——启示文学使用象征语言不等于可以任意赋予含义。格兰特·奥斯邦（Grant Osborne）在其《启示录注释》中指出，正确的启示录解经必须考虑旧约背景、一世纪历史处境和体裁特征。李万熙的解经完全脱离了这些释经原则。此外，新天地以隐秘渗透著称——信徒被训练隐瞒自己的新天地身份，潜入正统教会进行「收割」（拉人），这种欺骗性做法本身就违背了圣经的诚实原则（弗4:25）。",
    "core_argument_en": "Shincheonji Church of Jesus was founded by Korean Lee Man-hee in 1984. The organization claims Revelation's prophecies have 'actually fulfilled' in Lee and Shincheonji — Lee is the 'overcomer' of Revelation 2-3, the only one who can unseal Revelation, and Shincheonji's 144,000 will form the eschatological spiritual Israel. The core problem is extreme allegorical private interpretation. Every Revelation image is assigned a specific real-world correspondence: 'sun' means a particular pastor, 'stars' mean certain believers. Yet as Gordon Fee and Douglas Stuart stress in 'How to Read the Bible for All Its Worth,' the primary interpretive principle is respecting original context and genre — apocalyptic literature's symbolic language doesn't mean meanings can be arbitrarily assigned. Grant Osborne's Revelation commentary notes proper interpretation must consider OT background, first-century context, and genre features. Lee's hermeneutics completely abandons these principles. Furthermore, Shincheonji is notorious for covert infiltration — members are trained to conceal their Shincheonji identity and infiltrate orthodox churches for 'harvesting' (recruitment), a deceptive practice that itself violates Scripture's honesty principle (Eph 4:25).",
