        "objection_zh": "使徒行传明明记载奉耶稣的名受洗，为什么你们不遵行？",
        "objection_en": "Acts clearly records baptism in Jesus' name — why don't you follow this?",
        "response_zh": "使徒行传2:38的「奉耶稣基督的名」与马太福音28:19的三一名并不矛盾。「奉某人的名」在犹太文化中意为「靠着某人的权柄」，而非洗礼时只念一个名字。使徒行传强调的是洗礼的权柄来自基督，而非设立一个替代马太福音28:19的新公式。正如F.F.布鲁斯（F.F. Bruce）在其使徒行传注释中所解释的，两者是互补的而非矛盾的。",
        "response_en": "Acts 2:38's 'in the name of Jesus Christ' doesn't contradict Matthew 28:19's Trinitarian name. 'In someone's name' in Jewish culture means 'by someone's authority,' not reciting only one name during baptism. Acts emphasizes baptism's authority comes from Christ, not establishing an alternative formula to Matthew 28:19. As F.F. Bruce explains in his Acts commentary, both are complementary, not contradictory."
